  "prompt": "Do women lactate when they are pregnant?",
  "response": "Yes, women can start lactating during pregnancy, although it's more common towards the end of pregnancy or after giving birth. This early\u4e73\u6c41 is called colostrum, which is rich in nutrients and antibodies, providing essential nourishment and protection for newborns. However, not all women will experience lactation during pregnancy, and it's entirely normal if it doesn't happen until after delivery.",
